        <div id="pageContentInstallPlugin" class="page-content">
            <h2 id="ssylka1">Install Jira Plugin</h2>

            <p>The "JBehave for Jira" plugin can be installed via the Jira's built in "Add-on Management"
                functionality</p>

            <p>1. Navigate to "Add-ons" section from the administration menu and then click on "Find New
                Add-ons" from the menu on the left</p>

            <p class="fig">
                <img src="images/installation/Install%20Jira%20Plugin%20-%201.png" width="800" height="480"
                     alt="Иллюстрация">
            </p>

            </br>
            <p>2. In the search field type in 'JBehave for Jira' and then click on either "Buy Now" or "Free
                Trial" against the "Jbehave for Jira" plugin entry. Follow the prompts from then on to
                complete
                the installation.
            </p>

            <p class="fig">
                <img src="images/installation/Install%20Jira%20Plugin%20-%202.png" width="800" height="480"
                     alt="Иллюстрация">
            </p>

            <p>Note: if you are running an older version of Jira that does not come with the built in plugin
                manager functionality then please contact us for an alternative way on how to install this
                plugin in your Jira instance. </p>
            <hr>
            <br>
        </div>

        <div id="pageContentConfigurePlugin" class="page-content">
            <h3 id="ssylka2">Enable Plugin for a Jira project </h3>

            <p>1. Once the plugin has successfully been installed you will need to enable it for a specific Jira
                project. To do so go the "Manage Add-ons" page in the Administration area and then click on
                "Configure" button against "JBehave for Jira" plugin entry. </p>


            <p class="fig">
                <img src="images/inst6.png" width="800" height="480" alt="Иллюстрация">
            </p>

            <p>2. In the opened plugin configuration screen, select General tab and then select the projects
                that you want to have the plugin enabled for and click the relevant arrow button to move it
                to the enabled projects box and then click Apply Changes button.
            </p>
            <hr>
        </div>


        <div id="pageContentInstallClient" class="page-content">

            <h2 id="ssylka3"> Download Plugin Client </h2>

            <p>The plugin requires a Java client to work, which comes in the form of a Jar file that you
                need to
                have on your class path when running your JBehave tests. It can be downloaded from <a
                        href="https://bitbucket.org/pristrom/jbehave-for-jira-example-project/downloads">this</a>
                location.</p>

            <p>Maven users - the client library will soon be available for download from the maven central
                repository. Watch this space for an update.</p>

            <hr>
            <br>
        </div>

        <div id="pageContentConfigureClient" class="page-content">

            <h2 id="ssylka4">Configure JBehave runner</h2>

            <p>For the plugin client to exchange data with the plugin running in your Jira instance you need
                to
                make the following changes to your JBehave Embedder (runner):</p>

            <p>1. Use <strong>JiraStoryPathsFinder</strong> implementation to find story paths</p>

            <p class="fig">
                <img src="images/installation/Configure%20runner%20-%20JiraStoryPathsFinder.png"
                     width="800"
                     height="705"
                     alt="Иллюстрация">

            </p>

            <p>2. Set <strong>JiraStoryLoader</strong> as the StoryLoader implemenation to use in your
                embedder's configuration
            </p>

            <p class="fig">
                <img src="images/installation/Configure%20runner%20-%20JiraStoryLoader.png"
                     width="850"
                     height="580"
                     alt="Иллюстрация">

            </p>

            <p>3. Set <strong>JiraStoryReporter</strong> as the StoryReporter implementation to use in your
                embedder's configuration</p>

            <p class="fig">
                <img src="images/installation/Configure%20runner%20-%20JiraStoryReporter.png"
                     width="850"
                     height="580"
                     alt="Иллюстрация">

            </p>


            <p>4. Set <strong>JiraStepdocReporter</strong> as the StepDocReporter implemenattion to use in
                your
                embedder's configuration, and then call reportStepdocs method on the Embedder instance after
                executing your story tests</p>

            <p class="fig">
                <img src="images/inst5.png"
                     width="963"
                     height="961"
                     alt="Иллюстрация">

            </p>

            <p>A complete example project that contains the above changes applied can been downloaded from
                <a
                        href="https://bitbucket.org/pristrom/jbehave-for-jira-example-project/src">this</a>
                location.</p>
        </div>

